.ident	"@(#)proto:locale/C/menus/help/dttimezone	1.6"
.related kbhelp genhelp datetime
.title Help: Date and Time
ABOUT THE DATE AND TIME MENU
Use this menu to check that the current date and time are set
on your computer and to change them if necessary.  You can
also select the appropriate timezone.

TIMEZONE CONFIGURATION
To view or change the current timezone:
   1.  Use the <Tab> or arrow keys to move to the Timezone
       field, then press <F2>.

       A list of continents is displayed.  An asterisk (*)
       is shown next to the continent where the current
       timezone resides.
                                   (CONTINUED)
.page
   2.  To change the continent, use the <Tab> or arrow keys
       to move the asterisk to the appropriate field; then
       press <Enter>.

        A list of timezones is displayed.  An asterisk (*)
        is shown next to the current timezone.

   3.  To change the timezone, use the <Tab> or arrow keys
       to move the asterisk to the appropriate field; then
       press <Enter>.

       Do not worry about daylight savings laws when using
       this field.
                                   (CONTINUED)
.page
EXITING THE DATE AND TIME MENU
Press <F10> to enter your changes and exit the Date and Time
menu.

EXITING HELP
Press <Esc> to return to the Date and Time menu.
Press <F1> for more help.
